uch regrets that "America" has such a neutral a-political character. What is needed, he thinks, is vigorous political propaganda.





Sincerely yours,

(Mrs. Vladimir Nabokov)





TO: OLIVER CALDECOTT1

CC, 1 p.





1820 Montreux, Palace Hotel

October 18, 1971

